About IMGS 2017

   17th International Medical Geography Symposium

   The International Medical Geography Symposium is the leading
   international meeting of health and medical geographers. Every two
   years, the symposium welcomes health geographers and others interested
   in applying a spatial approach to their research to share findings and
   form new ideas about the progress of this exciting sub-discipline.

   The 17th IMGS will take place in France in July 2-7, 2017, hosted by
   University of Angers. The organizing committee welcomes all those
   interested in health geography to attend this conference. The theme of
   this edition is "Practicing health and medical geography in 2017".
   Papers and posters presented at the conference will deal with a variety
   of health issues, including: social perspectives on health; health
   policy; health care and services; ageing; urban health; rural health;
   environment and health; GIS approaches; global health; health human
   resources and health inequities and inequalities.

   Deadline to submit an abstract : February 25th, 2017
   Read the call for communications

University of Angers

   The University of Angers offers more than 300 different degree programs
   in all major academic fields and welcomes 19,000 students each year.

Commitees

   This event is organized by French health geographers from many
   universities and research institutes:
     * Sophie Baudet-Michel, Université Paris Diderot, Géographie-cités
     * Audrey Bochaton, Université Paris Ouest La Défense, LADYSS
     * Emmanuel Bonnet, IRD, Résiliences
     * Hélène Charreire, Université Paris Est, LabUrba
     * Virginie Chasles, Université Lyon 3, HESPER
     * Emmanuel Eliot, Université Rouen, IDEES
     * Sébastien Fleuret, CNRS, ESO-Angers
     * Florence Fournet, IRD, MIVEGEC
     * Clélia Gasquet-Blanchard, EHESP
     * Anne-Cécile Hoyez, CNRS, ESO-Rennes
     * Vincent Laperrière, Aix-Marseille Université, ESPACE
     * Véronique Lucas-Gabrielli, IRDES
     * Stéphane Rican, Université Paris Ouest la Défense, LADYSS
     * Alain Vaguet, Université Rouen, IDEES
     * Julie Vallée, CNRS, Géographie-cités

   The organizing committee draws on the expertise of a scientific
   committee comprising:
     * Mabel Carabali (Colombie)
     * Valorie Crooks (Vancouver, Canada)
     * Sarah Curtis (Durham, UK)
     * Pascal Handschumacher (IRD, France)
     * Robin Kearns (Auckland, Nouvelle-Zélande)
     * Thomas Kistemann (Bonn, Allemagne)
     * Hénock Blaise Nguendo-Yongsi (Cameroun)
     * Sarah Mc Lafferty (Univ Illinois, USA)
     * François Taglioni (La Réunion, France)

   A number of volunteers are working hard to make the IMGS 2017 a
   wonderful and memorable event. Thanks to everybody.
